{
  "texts": [
    "As before, these tools are available for a limited set of languages and AI systems.ChainForge [44] is a visual prompt testing tool that can be used to evaluate the result of prompts and prompt variations in different language models.",
    "This tool is intended for evaluation purposes, offering tools such as response evaluators or generating graphs for visualizing results.",
    "However, Chain-Forge (a) does not aim to adapt a prompt to different models (e.g., enabling the definition of language model-independent prompts and (b) is intended for testing only.Finally, approaches such as [45] and tools like PromptPerfect [46] and Promptist [47] explore the idea of optimizing user prompts for specific platforms, though this optimization is automatic and therefore opaque to the prompt designer.",
    "The automatic generation of prompts is also subject of investigation [11,48] so far with limited results.Impromptu aims to gather the best ideas of these approaches to provide the first platform-independent prompt DSL together with the infrastructure to assist in the creation of prompts and their versioning and automatic transformation to specific concrete target platforms providing, this way, an integrated comprehensive platform for prompt engineering.",
    "Solving complex tasksScenarios where large volumes of information need to be consumed to generate an answer or the solution involves combining several intermediate steps require more elaborate generative AI pipelines."
  ]
}